        <num>CC 1782</num>
        <heading>1782.  If the obligor is insolvent</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1782.  If the obligor is insolvent
When the obligation is such that its performance requires the solvency of the obligor, the term is regarded as nonexistent if the obligor is found to be insolvent.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109017</p>
